The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Gems, textiles see rebound in exports 
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Gems, textiles see rebound in exports 
          R. SURYAMURTHY                              
	New Delhi, Nov. 25: Exports of labour-intensive items such as gems and jewellery and textiles are picking up.        
	Gems and jewellery exports, the largest foreign exchange earner, are expected to grow 5 per cent after contracting for the most of last year.        
	The job scene in these labour-intensive segments have improved, too  around 4 lakh of the 5 lakh jobs lost last year have been restored, according to statistics for July-September 2009.         
	We expect to end the fiscal with exports of over $25 billion and a growth of 5 per cent. The order books for the current and the next quarters are good, Sabyasachi Ray, executive director of the Gem amp; Jewellery Export Promotion Council, told The Telegraph.        
	Gems exports grew a modest 1.45 per cent during 2008-09 to $21.1 billion from $20.8 billion in 2007-08. The sector witnessed a loss of over three lakh jobs during the last six months of last year.         
	Gems accounted for 15 per cent of the total merchandise exports of $168 billion in 2008-09. The government expects exports to touch $165-175 billion during 2009-10.        
	According to a labour survey, around five lakh jobs were added during the July-September quarter in labour-intensive sectors such as textiles, leather, metal, automobiles, gems and jewellery, transport and information technology.         
	The study is based on a survey of 2,873 units in 11 states.        
	Harish Rawat, minister of state for labour and employment, informed the Rajya Sabha, through a letter, that between October 2008 and September 2009, there has been a net addition of 1.51 lakh jobs in select sectors.                                                                                                                                       
